"title": "8650: hands, lifting up of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8650: hands, lifting up of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A human gesture which can be a sign of worship and adoration or indicate the swearing of a solemn oath. God is portrayed as raising his hands as a sign of authority over his creation.</p>\n<h2>God's uplifted hand</h2>\n<h3>God's uplifted hand signifies his power</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps118:16\">PSA 118:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:11\">EXO 24:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:13\">PSA 89:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:12\">ISA 9:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:17\">ISA 9:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:21\">ISA 9:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa26:11\">ISA 26:11</a></p>\n<h3>God's uplifted hand signifies his judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:25\">ISA 5:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam6:3\">1SA 6:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam6:5\">1SA 6:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa19:16\">ISA 19:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic5:9\">MIC 5:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech2:9\">ZEC 2:9</a></p>\n<h2>Hands uplifted for swearing oaths</h2>\n<h3>Oaths taken by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:5\">EZK 20:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:8\">EXO 6:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:40-Deut32:41\">DEU 32:40–32:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:15\">NEH 9:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:15\">EZK 20:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:7\">EZK 36:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek47:14\">EZK 47:14</a></p>\n<h3>Oaths taken by people and angels</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen14:22-Gen14:23\">GEN 14:22–14:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan12:7\">DAN 12:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev10:5\">REV 10:5</a></p>\n<h2>Hands uplifted in worship</h2>\n<h3>Hands lifted up in prayer</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps28:2\">PSA 28:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod17:11-Exod17:13\">EXO 17:11–17:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps141:2\">PSA 141:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:19\">LAM 2:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:41\">LAM 3:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:8\">1TI 2:8</a></p>\n<h3>Hands lifted up in praise</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps63:4\">PSA 63:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh8:6\">NEH 8:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:48\">PSA 119:48</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps134:2\">PSA 134:2</a></p>\n<h2>Hands lifted up for blessing</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev9:22\">LEV 9:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:50\">LUK 24:50</a></p>\n<h2>Hands lifted up as a threat</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam24:6\">1SA 24:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:17\">1SA 18:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam22:17\">1SA 22:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam24:10\">1SA 24:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam18:12\">2SA 18:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam18:28\">2SA 18:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam20:21\">2SA 20:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job31:21\">JOB 31:21</a></p>\n<h2>Uplifted hands as a sign of minimal effort</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:44\">GEN 41:44</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:32\">DEU 28:32</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra6:12\">EZR 6:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps76:5\">PSA 76:5</a></p>\n<h2>Uplifted hands as a sign of support</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps91:12\">PSA 91:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:6\">MAT 4:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:11\">LUK 4:11</a></p>",
